# Linux-30-Days-challenge
Hands-On Tasks (Try Yourself)
Task 1: Create a User with Non-Interactive Shell
Create a user who cannot log in to the system (used for services).
sudo useradd -s /sbin/nologin ammar
Verify: grep ammar /etc/passwd

Task 2: Create a Service User without Home Directory
Create a lightweight user without a home folder.
sudo useradd -M serviceuser
Check: ls /home

Task 3: Create a Temporary User with Expiry
Create a user that automatically expires after a specific date.
sudo useradd -e 2026-12-31 tempuser
Verify expiry: chage -l tempuser

Notes-
adduser vs useradd (Simple Difference)
adduser
Easy to use
Asks questions (password, name, etc.)
Creates home directory automatically
Used for normal users (humans)
useradd
No questions (runs directly)
Gives full control (you decide options)
Used for scripts, automation, service users
Simple way to remember
adduser → for humans
useradd → for automation
